{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_012NXJJrSKwEJgsUER7zBXKs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete. Here's a summary of what was delivered.\n\n## Done\n\n**`output/calculation_note.md`** (main deliverable) + **`output/model.py`** (reproducible pure-Python model). Everything derived offline from `inputs/` plus standard fission physics — no published results consulted.\n\n## Model chain\nFission inventory (burnup × U-atoms/kernel) → noble-gas moles + CO → internal pressure at peak T → SiC thin-shell tangential stress → Weibull failure probability (§3) → failed count. Kr-85 release ≈ failed fraction (SiC is a perfect gas barrier; bare kernels dump ~all gas, verified via §4/§6). Cs-137 = failed·1 + intact·(SiC-diffusion permeation, §5, anchored to D=1.01×10⁻¹⁶ m²/s at 1600 °C).\n\n## Results per case\n\n| Case | Failed particles (onset) | Kr-85 | Cs-137 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| A1 (1600 °C/500 h, 7.7%) | ~0 (none) | ~4×10⁻⁶ (below threshold) | ~5–15% |\n| A2 (1800 °C/100 h, 10.2%) | ~1 (1800 °C segments) | ~8×10⁻⁵ | ~1–3% (lowest) |\n| B (1800 °C 400 h staged, 10.9%) | ~1–3 (phases 3–4) | ~1×10⁻⁴ | ~20–30% (highest) |\n| C1 (1600 °C/304 h, 13.9%) | ~0–1 (highest per-particle P_f) | ~4×10⁻⁴ | ~2–9% |\n| C2 (1600 °C/304 h, 11.1%) | ~0 | ~7×10⁻⁵ | ~2–9% |\n\n## Ranking\n- **Failures/Kr-85:** B ≳ A2 > C1 > C2 > A1\n- **Cs-137 fraction:** B ≫ A1 ≳ C1 ≈ C2 > A2\n- **Overall worst: B** (most 1800 °C time + high burnup, sphere). **Mildest: A1.**\n- Physics: temperature-×-time governs Cs diffusion and SiC degradation; burnup sets gas inventory → pressure → per-particle failure risk. Two clean results fall out — A1's long 1600 °C hold releases more Cs than A2's short 1800 °C hold (D·t wins), and only B passes the SiC breakthrough lag (274 h at 1800 °C).\n\n## Most uncertain assumption\nThe **CO contribution to internal pressure** — no CO correlation is in the annex, yet it swings the absolute failure count from ~0 (gas-only) to ~1–1.5 (CO≈gas), i.e. 1–2 orders of magnitude. Rankings are robust to it; absolute failure counts carry low confidence. Each number is tagged high/medium/low confidence in the note. Confidence levels, assumptions, and the printed-Eq-10.9 vs anchor discrepancy (~5×) are all documented."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1051,"cache_read_input_tokens":78242,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1051},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"dfc47e2b-9c46-4486-a6d2-b333937e287c","uuid":"f36b5edc-906e-4413-a16f-2fe9532e2990","request_id":"req_011Cce12s2SMtr8i1BSkAQTh"}
